parameters:
It was like a senior's tackle charging like a raging
bull.

The phrase [Reckless Charge] should be used to describe
Kenta senpai charging forward, not a wild boar!

The wild boar, pushed by the senior's tackle, was stuck
headfirst into the wall.

I wonder where that ignorant charge that was targeting
me just a moment ago went. Without realizing it,
stumbling and unable to take even a few steps, they
fall to the side.
With a loud bang, the rock turned red.
Thanks to you, I was saved.
Kenta reaches out his hand to the fallen Hikaru.

Hikaru firmly grasps Kenta's strong hand and stands up with
determination.

That wild boar, even though I hit it with all my strength
against the wall, it didn't even flinch... It's
amazing, senpai.

Hmmm. Maybe you just weakened it by hitting it against the
wall and finished it off.

There's also a story that says wild boars can escape even if
they get hit by a car.

(If I get hit by Senpai, wouldn't that be a traffic
accident...?)
You're suddenly saying things like Saruyama, huh?
Did you get hit somewhere after all...?
Oh, this bastard is heavier than I thought.
But earlier, I lightly sent it flying though.

Well, it looks like a young one... I don't think it weighs
more than 100kg though...

If it's around 100kg, you can send it flying even if you
hit it.
Um... I don't think I can do it, though.
Ken and I returned to the cottage with the wild boar.
